<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Bean Soup</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>None</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>slices</unit></amt>
        <item>Bacon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Baked or boiled beans</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Cold water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Flour</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Salt; pepper, paprika</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Butter</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Cook bacon, add to beans, add cold water and cook until beans are soft,
  then rub them through a strainer. Place on the fire and add alittle more
  water if needed, the soup must not be too thick. Combine with the flour and
  butter. Cook 2 or 3 minutes. Season with salt, a dash of pepper, and
  paprika.
  
  I got this recipe from a friend and it's quite good.
  Posted to EAT-L Digest  by Russellyn Crombie &lt;DJJRS@AOL.COM&gt; on Sep 4, 1997
 
</step></directions></recipe></recipeml>
